goroad" part of the path is missing.</p>\n<p>(2) appears to correctly use the Wordpress Misc setting for "Store uploads in this folder". However, since (1) uploaded it to the wrong spot, the WPTouch admin code never sees the upload. If I move the files from "wp-content/uploads/wptouch/custom-icons/" to "wp-content/uploads/jungoroad/wptouch/custom-icons/" then WPTouch admin happily and correctly sees and uses the icon.\n</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"diablodale";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:12;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:27:"\n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"yotraxx on "Footer issue ?"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:63:"http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/topic/footer-issue#post-491";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 04 Apr 2010 21:37:31 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"491@http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:480:"<p>Hello there ! </p>\n<p>I''m currently using wPtouch 1.9.9.8 on my own blog (www.zmotion.fr) but have a problem: When using wptouch, footer seems to be VERY centered on a huge horizontal page...</p>\n<p>I''ve tried to edit footer.php without success. It seems the problem doesn''t come from there (I''ve putted away the "center" things for instance). Precision: I''m a noob in php... Could you gently explain me how to fix it ? What file have I to edit for working ?</p>\n<p>Thanks\n</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"yotraxx";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:13;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:27:"\n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"rayaddison on "wp-load.php problem"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/topic/wp-loadphp-problem#post-490";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 04 Apr 2010 16:46:02 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"490@http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2128:"<p>I''ve installed the WPtouch plugin on my Wordpress blog which is located in a subfolder on my domain. So I can display related posts on pages in the root of the domain, I call the wp-load.php file.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.rayaddison.com" rel="nofollow">http://www.rayaddison.com</a> (main site)<br />\n<a href="http://www.rayaddison.com/blog" rel="nofollow">http://www.rayaddison.com/blog</a> (wordpress installation)</p>\n<p>To call the posts on pages in the root I use;</p>\n<p>&lt;?php require(''blog/wp-load.php''); ?&gt;</p>\n<p>I then display them on the page using;</p>\n<p> &lt;?php<br />\n $postslist = get_posts(''numberposts=5&amp;order=DEC&amp;orderby=date'');<br />\n foreach ($postslist as $post) :<br />\n    setup_postdata($post);<br />\n ?&gt; </p>\n<li>&lt;div id="recentposts_img"&gt;<br />\n <a>" rel="bookmark" title="&lt;?php the_title_attribute(); ?&gt;" style=" text-decoration:none"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.rayaddison.com/scripts/timthumb/timthumb.php?src=&lt;?php echo catch_that_image() ?&gt;&amp;h=31&amp;w=31&amp;zc=1" width="31" height="31" alt="&lt;?php the_title(); ?&gt;" /&gt;</a><br />\n &lt;/div&gt;<br />\n &lt;div id="recentposts_txt"&gt;<br />\n <a>" rel="bookmark" title="&lt;?php the_title_attribute(); ?&gt;"&gt;&lt;?php the_title(); ?&gt;</a><br />\n &lt;/div&gt;</p>\n</li>\n<p> &lt;?php endforeach; ?&gt;</p>\n<p>Everything works perfectly except;</p>\n<p>When I have the Wptouch plugin active, I view the pages in my root domain on an iPhone and the posts do not display. On looking at the code (using Safari Developer Menu) I can see the error as;</p>\n<p>&lt;b&gt;Fatal error&lt;/b&gt;:  Call to undefined function  catch_that_image() in &lt;b&gt;/home/rayaddis/public_html/includes/footer.php&lt;/b&gt; on line &lt;b&gt;47&lt;/b&gt;</p>\n<p>When I disable the WPtouch plugin, the page will display properly on an iPhone.</p>\n<p>I think the iPhone detection causes the /blog/wp-load.php to fail - using an absoute URL causes the site to fail so is not an option.</p>\n<p>I''ve had to disable the plugin until I can get this fixed.</p>\n<p>Does anyone have a good suggestion for a fix/workaround?\n</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"rayaddison";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8: