e a page Blog --&gt; from a template "Blog" I have created<br />\nI use the following syntax (wp_query)<br />\n&lt;?php<br />\n/*<br />\nTemplate Name: Blog<br />\n*/<br />\n?&gt;<br />\n......<br />\n&lt;?php<br />\n$temp = $wp_query;<br />\n$wp_query= null;<br />\n$wp_query = new WP_Query();<br />\n$wp_query-&gt;query(''&amp;showposts=5''.''&amp;paged=''.$paged);<br />\nif ($wp_query-&gt;have_posts()) : while ($wp_query-&gt;have_posts()) : $wp_query-&gt;the_post();<br />\nglobal $more; $more = 0;<br />\n?&gt;<br />\n................<br />\ninstead of<br />\n&lt;?php if(have_posts()) : while(have_posts()) : the_post(); ?&gt;<br />\n................<br />\n&lt;?php endwhile; ?&gt;<br />\n&lt;?php $wp_query = null; $wp_query = $temp; ?&gt;</p>\n<p>instead of<br />\n&lt;?php endwhile; ?&gt;</p>\n<p>My Home page is a static page</p>\n<p>On my iPhone, using WPTouch template --&gt; I don''t have the posts (nothing)<br />\nif I shift to Mobile Theme OFF, it is working correctly</p>\n<p>Any ideas ?</p>\n<p>Best regards\n</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"dentaoman";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:19;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:27:"\n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"clavalle on "WPTouch and qTranslate"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/topic/wptouch-and-qtranslate#post-482";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 02 Apr 2010 14:37:48 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"482@http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1462:"<p>Hello everybody. I just installed WPTouch, it is incredible! And so, first of all congratulations.<br />\nAs post subject says, I found a workaround to let wpTouch and qTranslate live together :-)</p>\n<p>Before this workaround, I noticed that links in home section reported all translated titles, instead of the only one that fits current language.. something like this:</p>\n<p>ItalyItalia</p>\n<p>as you probably know qTranslate uses his own tags inside each post to distinguish different language titles<br />\n<code>&lt;!--:en--&gt;Italy&lt;!--:--&gt;&lt;!--:it--&gt;Italia&lt;!--:--&gt;</code></p>\n<p>Well, all I did is replace this piece of code (line 37 of themes/core/core-functions.php)</p>\n<p><code>echo(&#39;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&#39; . get_permalink($p[&#39;ID&#39;]) . &#39;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;&#39; . $image . &#39;&quot; alt=&quot;icon&quot; /&gt;&#39; . $p[&#39;post_title&#39;] . &#39;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#39;);</code> </p>\n<p>with this:</p>\n<p><code>echo(&#39;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&#39; . get_permalink($p[&#39;ID&#39;]) . &#39;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;&#39; . $image . &#39;&quot; alt=&quot;icon&quot; /&gt;&#39; . __($p[&#39;post_title&#39;]) . &#39;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#39;);</code></p>\n<p>I hope this could help someone and maybe see in some next version of wpTouch plugin.</p>\n<p>PS. So far I didn''t found any other issue about qTranslate compatibility, maybe you know where looking for others hidden places.\n</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"clavalle";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:20;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:27:"\n     \n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"akamichaelmusic on "Cannot upload custom icons"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/topic/cannot-upload-custom-icons#post-479";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 01 Apr 2010 16:11:35 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"479@http://www.bravenewcode.com/support/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:246:"<p>Has anyone figured out a resolution to this? I''m still having problems in version 1.9.9.8 - Upload is successful but, not updating in the pool.</p>\n<p>Help!</p>\n<p>UPDATE- I fixed it. I simply uploaded the files directly to the icon pool.\n</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"akamichaelmusic";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:21;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:27:"\n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n      \n    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"mebla